05/12/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- US Ambassador to Albania Marcie Ries is calling for fair and democratic elections in the country next year. 
Talking to the local TV Klan, Ries stressed Albania must observe international standards, when the next parliamentary voting takes place. 
She also stressed that all political parties are expected to assume responsibility for ensuring fair elections. 
Washington has offered $400,000 in assistance to help prepare for the vote. 
(Albanian News - 04/12/04)
